text: Milford is an unincorporated community in BakerCounty, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== A post office called Milford was established in 1852, and remained in operation until 1955. The community took its name from a gristmill at a ford on Itchawaynochaway Creek. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Baker County, Georgia Category:Unincorporated communities in Georgia (U.S. state)
title: Milford, Georgia
